ca.carleton.ccsl.meteorite
Class UAppRecord

java.lang.Object
  ca.carleton.ccsl.meteorite.UAppRecord
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class UAppRecord
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

The UAppRecord class is a Java Bean for storing UApp related details. Each UAppRecord corresponds to a package name/APK file installed on the users phone. The UAppRecord contains the package name, the path to the APK file, a hash of the APK file and the UAppID for the record.

Author:
dmccarney

Method Detail

getUAppID

public java.lang.String getUAppID()
Get the application's UAppID string. This value is a hash of: pkgName certHash1 certHash2 ... certHashN Each 'field' of the UAppID string is delimited by a space character. Depending on the app there may be 1 or more certificate hashes corresponding to the number of certificates used to sign the app.

Returns:
the uAppID

setUAppID

public void setUAppID(java.lang.String uAppID)

Parameters:
